I capture the mainWindows screen every 40ms to stream it to another computer. But the memory consumption rises and rises and at about 15 GB it slows down the webpage. 

```javascript
var handleScreenCapture = function(image) {
			image = null;
			setTimeout(screenTick, 40);
	}
	
	var screenTick = function() {
			mainWindow.capturePage({x:0,y:0, width:1920,height:360}, handleScreenCapture);
	}
		
	
	mainWindow.webContents.on('did-finish-load', function() {
		setTimeout(screenTick, 40);
	});
```
Is there a fix for that. Is it possible to garbage collect manually?

Thanks
Christoph

So I have been using Electron and Angular to make a software for myself. When I use the ipc module to send a message, I get an error that says <code>ipc.send is not a function</code>. Can someone please help? 
 
In app.js for Main Process:
````javascript 
 ipc.on('open-new-window', function(){
    var newWindow = new windowPart({
        width: 1280,
        height: 700,
        resizable: true,
        show: false
    });
    newWindow.loadUrl('file://' + __dirname + '/www/windows/newWindow.html');
    newWindow.maximize();
    newWindow.on('closed', function(){
        newWindow = null;
    });    
});
````

In index.js for the Renderer Process:
````javascript
$scope.openWindow = function(){
       ipc.send('open-new-window');
   };
````

In the index.html:
````html
 <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-block" ng-click="openWindow();"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-folder-open"></i> Open a new Window</button>
````

